Date: Mon, 8 Jun 2026 15:35:38 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] runtime: fix IC fast-path marker-transmute SIGSEGV (#59
 resurrection-at-scale)

try_call_bind_ic_fast (the CALL_BIND_IC_KIND_TYPE_CALL constructor inline-cache
fast path) read entry.fn_ptr and transmute'd it to a callable address and jumped.
For a class with no user __init__ that defines __del__, the resolved __init__ is
the inherited object.__init__, whose stored fn_ptr is a RUNTIME_CALLABLE_KEY_BASE
MARKER (0xFFFF_FF00_0000_0004), NOT a real code address. The slow fixed-arity
path decodes the marker via function_call_target_or_legacy_ptr (reading the
function object's call_target_ptr slot, set to the decoded real address at
construction); the IC fast path bypassed that slot and jumped to 0xFFFF...04 ->
SIGSEGV. The ~10-iteration threshold was the inline-cache warming (cold = slow
decode path = safe; warm = fast path fires the bad marker). Resurrection just
warmed the IC by repeatedly invoking object.__init__-class synthetics.

Fix routes the IC fast path through the SAME single decode authority as the slow
path (the council's single-decode-authority principle):
- function.rs: function_call_target_or_legacy_ptr made pub(crate).
- bind.rs try_call_bind_ic_fast: native arm computes
  call_addr = function_call_target_or_legacy_ptr(init_ptr, entry.fn_ptr) once;
  every native transmute site (closure + non-closure arms, arities 0-3) uses
  call_addr instead of raw entry.fn_ptr. wasm keeps entry.fn_ptr (lowers via the
  function-table trampoline, not a raw transmute). Variadic arms route through
  call_function_obj_vec (decodes internally).

Bug-class audit: try_call_bind_ic_fast was the ONLY raw-marker-transmute site.
The method IC (call_method_ic_dispatch) routes through call_function_obj_vec (no
raw transmute); native fixed-arity dispatchers obj0..obj5 decode via
call_native_fixed_arity!; the bare-transmute native obj6/obj7+ paths are
unreachable by markers (max marker arity is 5). Calling a raw runtime-callable
marker is now unrepresentable on the native IC fast path.

Adds the council's canonical 10-case resurrection regression matrix
(tests/differential/memory/resurrect_*). The IC fix is bug-class-complete: no
SIGSEGV at any N (was SIGSEGV past ~10), and the resurrection lifecycle state
machine is byte-identical to CPython 3.14 on native AND LLVM for the straight-line
cases (resurrect_once_N1, _then_final_drop, _with_field_refs,
_during_exception_unwind): __del__ runs exactly once (run-once verified), the
resurrected object is usable, inner field refs stay valid, and resurrection during
exception-unwind preserves exception propagation.

Three DISTINCT pre-existing defects (NOT the IC bug) block the remaining matrix
cases and are marked xfail (auto-flip to xpass when fixed), batoned in
project_task59_ic_marker_fixed_lifecycle_batons:
- loop-body finalizer-drop gap (NATIVE-Cranelift-only; byte-identical on LLVM):
  task #58 / design-27 ownership-lattice drop placement. N10/N1000/loop_stress/
  subclass_inherits_del.
- weakref subsystem (backend-agnostic): weakref.ref() does not resolve to live
  referents in compiled code, and gc.collect() clears weakrefs to container-held
  reachable objects. with_weakref.
- finalizer exception-swallow is composition-dependent (backend-agnostic):
  an exception in __del__ propagates instead of being swallowed when other
  finalizer classes precede it. with_exception_in_del.

Gates: molt-runtime --lib 510/0 (0 warn); molt-backend --features
"llvm native-backend" --lib 1107/0 (0 warn); memory corpus native 30/31
byte-identical (the 1 fail = pre-existing unrelated glob_iglob_bounded_rss os.walk
OOM item); round-12 finalizer suite byte-identical native+LLVM; peel 9/9 native +
9/9 LLVM; compliance 44 passed + 2 env-skipped (3.12 .venv) / 0 failed.

